def: Ready; directly forward; going before. [Obs.] "A forerightwind." Chapman.
Engaged in a quarrel; apt or disposed to quarrel; as,quarreling factions; a quarreling mood.-- Quar"rel*ing*ly, adv.
The quality of being a baby; the personality of an infant.
Wearied; tired; fatigued. [Obs.]Requickened what in flesh was fatigate. Shak.
A woolen stuff thinner than ratteen.
A bank; a fund. Mount of piety. See Mont de piété.
A tribe of Indians which formerly occupied the region ofNorthern Illinois, allied in language to the Sacs and Foxes.
One who takes care of baggage; a camp follower. [Obs.] Sir W.Raleigh.
Dark blue or bluish gray; lead-colored. [Scot.]
